# PitBoss

**The universal governance and certification platform for competitive sim racing leagues.**

PitBoss is a Progressive Web App that brings FIA-grade institutional structure to sim racing. Any league, any rulebook, any series. You upload your documents — PitBoss builds your certification system.

The Truth Racing League (TRL) and World Series Championship (WSC) are the Phase 1 proof of concept. Every role in both institutions must be certified through PitBoss before they can exercise any authority. No exam, no seat.

-----

## What It Does

PitBoss is the sole administrative authority for every league it hosts. It gatekeeps the grid, administers the law, and holds the record of truth.

**Certification Engine**
Every member — drivers, stewards, team principals, BSAC officers, technical directors, broadcast staff — must pass a role-specific exam before they can operate. Exams are AI-generated fresh on every attempt from the official rulebooks. No two exams are identical. Questions are pulled directly from the governing documents and calibrated across three difficulty tiers.

**Document Ingestion**
Drop in any rulebook — PDF, DOCX, TXT, or Markdown — and PitBoss reads it, extracts the rule structure, generates a system prompt, and builds a new exam automatically. New document in, new exam out.

**League Sovereignty**
Every league on PitBoss is a completely separate environment. TRL and WSC certifications, member registries, question banks, and tokens never cross unless explicitly enabled. Each league runs under its own rulebook, its own pass thresholds, and its own admin account.

**Security**
All score calculation is server-side. Certification tokens are server-side. Lockout timers are server-side. Clearing your cache changes nothing. The platform is the only authority.

