## Exam Mechanics

- Questions are generated by Claude AI (`claude-sonnet-4-20250514`) from the official rulebook content
- Every attempt generates a completely fresh question set — no repeats, no cached banks
- Timer is server-side — cannot be paused, bypassed, or reset by clearing cache
- Timer starts the moment the exam opens
- Exam auto-submits on timer expiry with answers given so far
- Steward exams include a mandatory Practical Incident Scenario after the main exam — this has its own timer that only starts after the main exam is submitted
- Score is calculated server-side only — never client-side
- Failed attempt → 24-hour server-side lockout before retake is available
- Passed attempt → certification token issued, visible on member profile

