## Document Ingestion Engine

PitBoss can build an exam from any document you upload. The pipeline:

1. **Upload** — Drop a PDF, DOCX, TXT, or Markdown file into the ingestion panel
1. **Extract** — PDF.js parses real text-layer PDFs page by page. mammoth.js handles DOCX. Plain text reads directly.
1. **Analyse** — Claude reads the extracted content and writes a structured exam system prompt, identifying key articles, rule areas, enforcement mechanisms, and focus topics
1. **Configure** — Set the league, role title, question count, time limit, pass mark, and tier
1. **Generate** — The exam is registered instantly. A new exam card appears in the portal. The exam works identically to all built-in exams.

Generated exams persist within the browser session and can be removed individually or cleared in bulk.

> Scanned/image-only PDFs cannot be extracted — PDF.js requires a text layer. All text-based PDFs, DOCX files, and plain text rulebooks work correctly.

