## Technical Stack

|Layer              |Technology                                                           |
|-------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Frontend           |HTML / CSS / Vanilla JS — PWA-ready                                  |
|Question generation|Claude API (`claude-sonnet-4-20250514`)                              |
|PDF extraction     |PDF.js 3.11.174 (Cloudflare CDN)                                     |
|DOCX extraction    |mammoth.js 1.6.0 (Cloudflare CDN)                                    |
|Hosting            |GitHub Pages                                                         |
|CORS proxy         |Cloudflare Worker (required for Anthropic API calls from the browser)|

### CORS Proxy Requirement

GitHub Pages serves static files only — it cannot make server-side API calls. All calls to the Anthropic API route through a Cloudflare Worker proxy. Without the proxy, question generation and document analysis will fail with a CORS error.

**Worker setup:**

1. Go to [dash.cloudflare.com](https://dash.cloudflare.com) → Workers & Pages → Create Worker
1. Paste the proxy script (see below)
1. Deploy — copy the worker URL
1. Replace `https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages` in the portal HTML with your worker URL

```javascript
export default {
  async fetch(request, env) {
    if (request.method === 'OPTIONS') {
      return new Response(null, {
        headers: {
          'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',
          'Access-Control-Allow-Methods': 'POST, OPTIONS',
          'Access-Control-Allow-Headers': 'Content-Type, x-api-key, anthropic-version',
        }
      });
    }

    const body = await request.json();
    const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'x-api-key': env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
        'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01',
      },
      body: JSON.stringify(body),
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    return new Response(JSON.stringify(data), {
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',
      }
    });
  }
};
```

Set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` as a Worker secret in the Cloudflare dashboard.

