## Philosophy

> *“Truth in Meritocracy: Your Seat is Earned, Not Given.”*

PitBoss originated from a real governance failure — a driver was poached, messages were edited, and there was no enforcement mechanism available. A third league was simultaneously observed muting members with no oversight structure.

The answer was not a better Discord server. The answer was institutional infrastructure.

TRL’s governance framework — the Charter, the BSAC, the Stewards Panel, the certification mandate — predates and mirrors what the FIA has now formally codified in Appendix E. PitBoss is the technology layer that makes it operational for community leagues worldwide.

The platform does not care what game you play, what series you model, or how big your league is. You bring your rulebook. PitBoss builds the institution.

